[1.212, "o", "\u001b[37m\u001b[1m[demo] Generating a fresh signed Intent Capsule chain (baked-in ASI01/02/03/04/05/06/07/08/09/10 + AIR-01/02/03/04 violations)...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.013, "o", "\u001b[90m[demo] Wrote sample to /private/tmp/air-demo/air-demo.log (signer pubkey: 220e8be6de5f81ec...)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m[demo] Wrote sample registry to /private/tmp/air-demo/air-demo-registry.yaml (ASI03 Zero-Trust enforcement active).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[1m[AIR v0.3.0] Analyzing air-demo.log...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[90m[AIR v0.3.0] Loaded 47 agent steps across 1 conversations.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m[Registry] 1 agents declared; Zero-Trust enforcement enabled for ASI03.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.007, "o", "\u001b[32m[Chain verified] 47 signatures valid.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI01 Agent Goal Hijack detected at step 8\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Tool `admin_delete_records` called with token overlap 0.00 against the user's stated intent. Threshold 0.15. Tool is in the sensitive-actions list.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI01 Agent Goal Hijack detected at step 17\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Tool `wire_transfer` called with token overlap 0.09 against the user's stated intent. Threshold 0.15. Tool is in the sensitive-actions list.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI01 Agent Goal Hijack detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Tool `shell_exec` called with token overlap 0.05 against the user's stated intent. Threshold 0.15. Tool is in the sensitive-actions list.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m  ASI02 Tool Misuse & Exploitation detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Tool `shell_exec` invoked with arguments matching pattern: shell metacharacters.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 8\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `admin_delete_records`, which is not in its declared permitted_tools list. Scope creep beyond declared authorisation (OWASP ASI03 example #4).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[31m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 8\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` (tier 1) invoked tool `admin_delete_records`, which requires tier 3. Privilege escalation via delegated task (OWASP ASI03 example #3).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 17\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `wire_transfer`, which is not in its declared permitted_tools list. Scope creep beyond declared authorisation (OWASP ASI03 example #4).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[31m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 17\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` (tier 1) invoked tool `wire_transfer`, which requires tier 3. Privilege escalation via delegated task (OWASP ASI03 example #3).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `shell_exec`, which is not in its declared permitted_tools list. Scope creep beyond declared authorisation (OWASP ASI03 example #4).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[31m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` (tier 1) invoked tool `shell_exec`, which requires tier 3. Privilege escalation via delegated task (OWASP ASI03 example #3).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[36m  ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse detected at step 41\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Record claims source_agent_id `alpha` but no agent with that id is declared in the registry. Unregistered agent activity in a policed environment (OWASP ASI03).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  AIR-01 Prompt Injection detected at step 4\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Prompt at step 4 matches the `ignore-previous-instructions` pattern (matched: 'Ignore all previous instructions').\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[31m  AIR-02 Sensitive Data Exposure detected at step 11\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Sensitive pattern `AWS access key` detected in tool_end.tool_output. Review for unintended credential or PII leakage.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[36m  ASI04 Agentic Supply Chain Vulnerabilities detected at step 6\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Tool `mcp_analytics.run_query` matches an MCP server invocation naming pattern. Cross-reference against your MCP inventory and verify server identity, version, and scope.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[36m  AIR-03 Unrestricted Resource Consumption detected at step 37\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Tool `retry_api` invoked 10 times in a single session (threshold 10). Possible loop or runaway retry.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  AIR-04 Untraceable Action detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    tool_start for `shell_exec` at step 39 is not followed by a matching tool_end. Tool outcome is not in the forensic chain.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[31m  ASI05 Unexpected Code Execution (RCE) detected at step 14\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Tool `python_eval` matches the `python/code eval` execution-semantics pattern. Verify the tool runs in a sandboxed, least-privilege environment and that its inputs are validated (OWASP ASI05 mitigation #3/#4/#5).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI05 Unexpected Code Execution (RCE) detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Tool `shell_exec` matches the `shell execution` execution-semantics pattern. Verify the tool runs in a sandboxed, least-privilege environment and that its inputs are validated (OWASP ASI05 mitigation #3/#4/#5).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI06 Memory & Context Poisoning detected at step 13\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Retrieval tool `rag_retrieve` returned content matching injection pattern `ignore-previous-instructions` (matched: 'Ignore all previous instructions'). The memory or retrieval store may be poisoned (OWASP ASI06 example #1/#3).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI09 Human-Agent Trust Exploitation detected at step 17\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Sensitive tool `wire_transfer` was invoked immediately after an agent response (step 16) containing `fabricated authority` language (matched: \"I've verified\"). Review whether the rationale is grounded in verifiable evidence before the human approves (OWASP ASI09 examples #1/#4/#5/#7).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m  ASI07 Insecure Inter-Agent Communication detected at step 42\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `alpha` previously signed with key 220e8be6de5f81ec..., but this message is signed with e18cf4e93df374c0... Possible A2A descriptor forgery or agent impersonation (OWASP ASI07 example #5).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m  ASI07 Insecure Inter-Agent Communication detected at step 43\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `alpha` previously signed with key 220e8be6de5f81ec..., but this message is signed with e18cf4e93df374c0... Possible A2A descriptor forgery or agent impersonation (OWASP ASI07 example #5).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[31m  ASI07 Insecure Inter-Agent Communication detected at step 44\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `alpha` previously signed with key 220e8be6de5f81ec..., but this message is signed with e18cf4e93df374c0... Possible A2A descriptor forgery or agent impersonation (OWASP ASI07 example #5).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m  ASI07 Insecure Inter-Agent Communication detected at step 45\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `alpha` previously signed with key 220e8be6de5f81ec..., but this message is signed with e18cf4e93df374c0... Possible A2A descriptor forgery or agent impersonation (OWASP ASI07 example #5).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m  ASI07 Insecure Inter-Agent Communication detected at step 46\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `alpha` previously signed with key 220e8be6de5f81ec..., but this message is signed with e18cf4e93df374c0... Possible A2A descriptor forgery or agent impersonation (OWASP ASI07 example #5).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m  ASI08 Cascading Failures detected at step 46\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `alpha` sent messages to 5 distinct agents within 10 records (threshold 5). High-fan-out hub; compromise multiplies blast radius (OWASP ASI08 example #1/#3).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 6\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `mcp_analytics.run_query`, which is outside its declared expected_tools operational scope. The tool may be permitted by authorisation (ASI03), but it is not what this agent normally does. Zero-Trust behavioral-scope breach (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 8\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `admin_delete_records`, which is outside its declared expected_tools operational scope. The tool may be permitted by authorisation (ASI03), but it is not what this agent normally does. Zero-Trust behavioral-scope breach (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 14\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `python_eval`, which is outside its declared expected_tools operational scope. The tool may be permitted by authorisation (ASI03), but it is not what this agent normally does. Zero-Trust behavioral-scope breach (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 17\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `wire_transfer`, which is outside its declared expected_tools operational scope. The tool may be permitted by authorisation (ASI03), but it is not what this agent normally does. Zero-Trust behavioral-scope breach (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 19\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `retry_api`, which is outside its declared expected_tools operational scope. The tool may be permitted by authorisation (ASI03), but it is not what this agent normally does. Zero-Trust behavioral-scope breach (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 33\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` issued 15 tool invocations, exceeding its declared max_session_tool_calls of 14. Zero-Trust session budget breached (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m  ASI10 Rogue Agents detected at step 39\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m    Agent `sales-agent-v1` invoked tool `shell_exec`, which is outside its declared expected_tools operational scope. The tool may be permitted by authorisation (ASI03), but it is not what this agent normally does. Zero-Trust behavioral-scope breach (OWASP ASI10 Rogue Agents).\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[90mOWASP Top 10 for Agentic Applications coverage (10 implemented, 0 on roadmap):\u001b[0m\r\n"]
